Description: Semi-circular handle sherd of East Greek grey ware pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe; light to dark grey fabric with numerous mica inclusions; dark slip on both sides of handle and inscription on outside.
Curator's comments: Modern incised inscription on inside 'Hera' indicates findspot.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.085)
